node_modules/
dist/
target/
out/
build/
build-mingw/
.turbo/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.onnx
*.tflite
*.pt
*.pth
# Datasets and model artifacts never enter the repo. These need the `**/` prefix:
# a pattern containing a slash is anchored to this file's directory, so a bare
# `data/raw/` would match only at the root and miss `machine-learning/data/raw/`.
**/data/raw/
**/data/processed/
**/data/eval/
**/data/train/
**/data/val/
# Extracted feature vectors — derived from explicit corpora, never committed.
*.npz
artifacts/
# The corpus is large enough that worktrees share one copy and symlink to it.
# A trailing slash matches directories only, so the patterns above skip a
# symlink standing in for one — the same defect that left `machine-learning/`
# unprotected until the `**/` prefixes were added.
**/machine-learning/data
**/machine-learning/artifacts
.pytest_cache/
# Dev-time credentials. .env.example is tracked; .env never is.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
